---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
import headshot from '../assets/headshot.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`About · ${site.name}`}
  description="Joshua Ford: NetSuite administrator, amateur radio operator (KJ5IRQ), and persistent tinkerer in Texas."
>
  <article class="about">
    <header>
      <p class="label">About</p>
      <h1>The operator</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          I'm Joshua Ford, a NetSuite administrator and amateur radio operator ({site.callsign})
          in Texas. I like systems that are understandable, and I build the missing pieces when
          they aren't. Usually tinkering with something.
        </p>

        <h2>The arc</h2>
        <p>
          I started in warehouse operations, learned the systems that ran the place, and kept
          following them upstream until I owned the ERP. Today I run NetSuite for a Texas ISP at
          the director level: workflow design, integration plumbing, and automation that has to
          survive real users.
        </p>
        <p>
          The same habit runs the rest of my life. My radio node has a REST API and an MCP server
          because I wanted to script it. My homelab exists so experiments break at home instead of
          anywhere that matters. The pattern is always the same: learn the system end to end, then
          automate the boring parts.
        </p>

        <h2>What I work with</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>NetSuite administration, workflows, and integrations</li>
          <li>Python, FastAPI, and small services that do one job well</li>
          <li>Model Context Protocol and practical, local-first AI tooling</li>
          <li>AllStarLink, EchoLink, and amateur radio infrastructure</li>
          <li>Proxmox, Linux, and home automation</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Reaching me</h2>
        <p>
          Email is best: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>. The code lives on
          <a href={site.github} rel="noopener">GitHub</a>, the resume version of me is on
          <a href={site.linkedin} rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>, and the callsign checks out on
          <a href={site.qrz} rel="noopener">QRZ</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <Image
        src={headshot}
        alt="Joshua Ford"
        width={400}
        widths={[400, 800]}
        sizes="(max-width: 800px) 60vw, 280px"
        class="about-photo"
      />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about header {
    padding-block: var(--space-8) var(--space-6);
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, var(--measure)) auto;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    align-items: start;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .about-photo {
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    width: 280px;
    height: auto;
    position: sticky;
    top: var(--space-6);
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-photo {
      width: 200px;
      position: static;
      order: -1;
    }
  }
</style>
